<h2 class="text-center" style="text-align: center;"> North Side in the News</h2>
<p style="text-align: center;">North Side was proud to have a story about our Virtual School televised by Fox 2 News on their 10 p.m. news broadcast April 20th.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://fox2now.com/news/principal-taps-into-community-to-help-his-students-be-able-to-e-learn/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch the coverage now. </a></p>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">Remote Learning until May 22nd</h3>
<div class="" data-block="true" data-editor="dqga3" data-offset-key="aspsn-0-0">
<div class="public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr" style="text-align: center;" data-offset-key="aspsn-0-0"><span data-offset-key="aspsn-0-0">Parents and Guardians: Grab-and-go food bags can be picked up from 8 a.m.-noon in the main building at the elementary school, Monday-Friday. For everyone's safety, please wear a mask or request a mask upon arrival. </span></div>
<div class="public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr" style="text-align: center;" data-offset-key="aspsn-0-0"> </div>
<div class="public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr" style="text-align: center;" data-offset-key="aspsn-0-0">If at this point you need a hotspot or laptop replacement/repair, please text or call Mr. Asher at 646-918-4616 to make arrangements.</div>
<div class="public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr" style="text-align: center;" data-offset-key="aspsn-0-0">We will get through this together.</div>
</div>
<hr>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="/virtual-school.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 28px;">– Virtual School Access Here –</span></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Visit our Virtual School Homepage for instructions on getting your scholar's laptop or tablet set up and how/when to contact your teachers for support. We have some great how-to videos that walk you through installing Google Chrome or accessing Google Classrooms.</span></p>
<hr>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="/empoweren74917.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 28px;">– Food Pick-up &amp; Delivery Schedule –</span></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Breakfasts and lunches for scholars will be available for pick-up from 8 a.m. until noon each weekday at the elementary school. Delivery is available during these hours in special circumstances.</span></p>
<h3 class="public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr" style="text-align: center;" data-offset-key="aspsn-0-0">Beyond Food: Support for Your Entire Family</h3>
<div class="public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr" style="text-align: center;" data-offset-key="aspsn-0-0">
<p>Is your family struggling due to COVID-related issues? Has your family experienced a death or contracted the illness? Lost income or childcare?</p>
<p>North Side wants to help.</p>
<p>We can offer a variety of resources depending on your situation. Please contact our social worker Ms. Allen, for discreet, compassionate support. Ms. Allen's cell is 314-324-1010.</p>
<p>Your situation will remain strictly between you and Ms. Allen unless you give permission to involve others in providing support. The exception is a known case of COVID-19 in your household which must be reported to the health department. </p>
</div>
<hr>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="/cmss_files/attachmentlibrary/Parent-Fliers/ClosureCorona3-16-20.pdf" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Coronavirus School Closing Notification Letter</a> – issued Monday, March 16, 2020</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Please, remember that anyone exhibiting symptoms of fever, coughing, and difficulty breathing should not be assumed to have COVID-19. However, if anyone in your family has a fever, please contact your doctor immediately.</p>
<hr>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">
<br>Want to work at the #1 public/charter school in St. Louis?</h3>
<p style="text-align: center;">Small class sizes, 15 or fewer students</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">High academic and behavior expectations</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="/careers.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Apply now for open positions.</a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"> </p>
<hr>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Beyond Expectations</span></h2>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">North Side is so much more than a #1 charter school and #1 public school in the City of St. Louis.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Our scholars are proof that children who find themselves in the most challenging zip codes of St. Louis can succeed far beyond expectations. Again and again, North Side scholars prove that with the right support and high expectations, they will rise above. </span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">The teachers and administrators at North Side believe that academic and character development go hand in hand. Scholars are instilled with an appreciation of our <a href="/academics.html">JUSTICE</a> character traits and a growth mindset that nurtures intellectual curiosity and resilience in the face of adversity and struggle. North Side's high expectations, small class sizes, and focus on family involvement make us a top-performing school, year after year. </p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">High Expectations | Small Class Sizes | Family Involvement</h3>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">North Side Community School is a free public school with open enrollment for children in pre-kindergarten through seventh grade. We focus on the whole child offering an exceptional academic and life experience. We put basic living needs and basic academic skills mastery high on our priority list with extended day enrichment programming and an extended school year further characterizing our approach to education.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">We are North Side Community School, where scholars seek knowledge and JUSTICE. Where scholars get the opportunity to learn and realize their true potential.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Come visit us and learn more.</p>
<hr>
<p style="text-align: center;">Did you know that online education access is the right of every student enrolled at North Side Community School or any Missouri public school? Learn more about Missouri's <a href="/cmss_files/attachmentlibrary/MOCAP-Guidance.pdf">MoCAP program</a>.</p>
